e past day the measure of a man is not how great his faith is but how great his love is we must not let government programs disconnect our souls from each other j c watts love faith great im not one that believes that affirmative action should be based on ones skin color or ones gender i think it should be done based on ones need because i think if you are from a poor white community i think that poor white kid needs a scholarship just as badly as a poor black kid j c watts community action black i think you grow wherever god plants you i hope im growing as a person of faith as a christian that should be our number one objective this journey of life that all starts with a personal intimate relationship with christ and then being in prayer every single day about all of those things  being tenacious about it j c watts life relationship journey everyone tries to define this thing called character its not hard character is doing whats right when nobodys looking j c watts character looking doing good policy makes good politics and what ive done has been good politics j c watts good politics done i would caution all of us or i would remind all of us that any candidate that we support they are going to be flawed j c watts support going caution when you look at the results that newt gingrich got when he was speaker he got results for the american people j c watts american look people theres a whole lot more to the africanamerican community than entertainment and sports j c watts sports community more having a republican candidate speak at the naacp convention is like trying to build a house starting at the roof if you dont have a foundation the roof isnt going to stand j c watts trying foundation speak republicans think that the naacp is the only voice in the black community it is a voice in the black community but its not the only voice j c watts community black voice when it comes to the american dream no one has a corner on the market all of us have an equal chance to share in that dream j c watts chance american dream in addition there is one title i cherish a great deal more than congressman and that is the title of dad j c watts dad great more i embrace my blackness just as i do my conservatism and my christianity but i dont want to be defined or pigeonholed by any one of the many elements that make up my character j c watts character want embrace im looking forward to the day when america will mature to the point that we are a colorblind society im not so sure that in politics that will ever be reality because politics has a way of separating us based on skin color j c watts politics day society reparations i believe are talked about for political reasons trying to cater for the purpose of getting votes if congress was serious about reparations  in  and  the democrats controlled the house the senate and the white house and not one single republican vote was needed for reparations j c watts purpose believe trying im secure in who i am i dont need the validation of those that would say you have to be a certain thing in order to be accepted im comfortable going against the grain if i need to j c watts i am you comfortable in my wildest imagination i never thought that the fifth of six children born to helen and buddy watts  in a poor black neighborhood in the poor rural community of eufaula oklahoma  would someday be called congressman j c watts children community black if you are explaining you are losing j c watts losing you explaining the democratic party has taken the black community for granted and said this is the most loyal constituency we have theyre not going anywhere but the republican party has said thats the most loyal constituency democrats have theyre not going anywhere weve got to win without them j c watts community black party individual responsibility hard work paying attention in school faith family all these things are important j c watts work family hard work share this page cite this page citation find on ama